  "why": "The paper applies mutations as explicit image-space operations (rotation, translation, shear, zoom, brightness, contrast) directly to training images and uses an on-the-fly Keras data generator to feed these augmented images into training (i.e., mutations operate in the raw input/pixel domain rather than in a latent/embedding space). However, the paper does not explicitly state that it enforces serialization/format constraints (e.g., clipping/rounding to integer [0,255] pixel ranges or converting to standard image file formats) or that it verifies that perturbations survive conversion to a serialized input format. Therefore the approach operates on raw input values (reducing sensitivity to the reproducibility problem) but lacks an explicit guarantee that perturbations will be preserved under serialization—matching the metric’s “Medium” description.",
